comp\u00e1\u00f1anos en esta transmisi\u00f3n completamente en espa\u00f1ol.\n\nLunes 8 de abril de 2024 1:30 p.m. EDT\n\nM\u00edralo en YouTube\n\nTelescope Feeds\n\n### Across the Path\n\nWatch a clean telescope feed of a total solar eclipse moving across North\nAmerica on April 8, 2024. Weather permitting, we will provide live views of\nthe eclipse from several locations across the eclipse path, including showing\nthe partially eclipsed Sun in different wavelengths of light.\n\nThese telescope feeds are provided courtesy of our partners and collaborators.\n\nWatch on YouTube\n\nLaunch Livestream\n\n### Sounding Rocket Launches\n\nNASA will launch three sounding rockets for the Atmospheric Perturbations\naround the Eclipse Path (APEP) mission from NASA's Wallops Flight Facility\nduring the April 8 total solar eclipse.\n\nThe launch window for the mission is 2:40 p.m.- 4:05 p.m. EDT. Rockets are\nscheduled to launch approximately 45 minutes apart. Coverage of the mission\nwill begin 10 minutes before the scheduled launch time.\n\nWatch on YouTube\n\nKeep Exploring\n\n## Discover More Topics From NASA\n\n2024 Total Eclipse\n\nNASA Eclipse Science\n\nTotal Solar Eclipse FAQ\n\nTotal Solar Eclipse Safety\n\nReturn to top\n\n### The National Aeronautics and Space Administration\n\nNASA explores the unknown in air and space, innovates for the benefit of\nhumanity, and inspires the world through discovery.\n\n  * About NASA's Mission\n\nJoin Us\n\n  * Home\n  * News & Events\n  * Multimedia\n  * NASA+\n  * Missions\n  * Humans in Space\n  * Earth & Climate\n  * The Solar System\n  * The Universe\n  * Science\n  * Aeronautics\n  * Technology\n  * Learning Resources\n  * About NASA\n  * NASA en Espa\u00f1ol\n\n### Follow NASA\n\n  * More NASA Social Accounts\n  * NASA Newsletters\n\n  * Sitemap\n  * For Media\n  * Privacy Policy\n  * FOIA\n  * No FEAR Act\n  * Office of the IG\n  * Budget & Annual Reports\n  * Agency Financial Reports\n  * Contact NASA\n  * Accessibility\n